BUSINESS REQUIREMENTS

The business requirements describe what the insurance company needs from the fraud detection system
in order to reduce losses and improve operational efficiency.

1️. FRAUD DETECTION SYSTEM

The system must be able to identify potentially fraudulent insurance claims based on historical claim data and customer information.

2️. AUTOMATED CLAIM ANALYSIS

The system should automatically analyze claim data such as:

*Policy details
*Customer information
*Incident details
*Claim amount
*Accident severity

3️. REAL-TIME FRAUD PREDICTION

The model should allow the company to predict fraud in real time when a new claim is submitted.

The system should classify claims as:

*Fraudulent
*Legitimate

4️. HIGH PREDICTION ACCURACY

The machine learning model should achieve high accuracy and reliability so that the company can trust the predictions while reviewing claims.

5️. RISK-BASED CLAIM PRIORITIZATION

The system should help investigators by flagging high-risk claims that require further investigation.
This allows the fraud investigation team to focus on suspicious claims first.

6️. EASY INTEGRATION

The fraud detection system should be able to integrate with the company’s existing claim management system.
This ensures smooth implementation without disrupting current business processes.

7️. DATA VISUALIZATION and REPORTING

The system should provide insights such as:

*Fraud patterns
*Fraud rate
*High-risk claim categories

8️. SCALABLE SOLUTION

The system should be scalable so it can handle large volumes of insurance claims in the future.

9️. USER-FRIENDLY INTERFACE

The application should provide a simple interface where users can input claim details and receive fraud predictions easily.

10. DATA SECURITY

The system should ensure secure handling of sensitive customer and insurance data to protect privacy and comply with regulations.

  BUSINESS OBJECTIVE

The main objectives of this project are:

*Detect fraudulent insurance claims using machine learning.
*Reduce financial losses caused by fraud.
*Improve the efficiency of claim processing.
*Assist investigators in identifying high-risk claims quickly.

